00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:15,600
from the writer and editor at the Mail who put the story together. I know a lot of editors at

92
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:20,480
the Mail and the nugget of science they understand is so small it can be drowned in their lunchtime

93
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:25,920
gins and tonics. They shouldn't be used as a credible source on this complicated aspect

94
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:31,600
of science. So once again I would urge internet lovers to be sceptical. Don't believe something

95
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:36,160
you read simply because it's in a tabloid newspaper. If it gives no source for the

96
00:08:36,160 --> 00:08:41,920
information, treat it with scepticism. If it does give a source, don't let the tabloid editors

97
00:08:41,920 --> 00:08:47,680
interpret it for you. Read the source yourself and check whether the interpretation you've been given

98
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:49,520
is accurate.

